HEADWORD: Polysulphide
<hw>Pol`y*sul"phide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets> + <ets>sulphide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A sulphide having more than one atom of sulphur in the molecule; --
contrasted with <xex>monosulphide</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

